Cognitive freedom (cf.~\ref{theorem:bk4_freedom_criterion}), as defined by self-regulated drift and reflective operator selection, is a necessary prerequisite for moral agency in symbolic systems. Without such self-regulation, behavior is merely reaction, not chosen action.
